Power was sucked out of my sisters and mother in one form another. #domesticviolence #sexualabuse #shame and #sadness ... these are the words that defined the ones nearest and dearest to me... including myself. There once was a fire in me, one that could light up a room and set it into flames from my passion alone. I keep trying to pinpoint a moment in time when that started to dim, and I realize it was gradual. It started with “you talk too much”, “nice girls...do X”, or that my looks were my greatest ASSet (implicitly on too many levels to count)... so, I shrank, I got smaller and things like normal, natural teenage acne crushed my self-perception. Was it vanity? No. A sick society, one that teaches women that building their ass is more important than building a strong mind. I was merely a product.Now, I attend therapy like it’s my fucking religion, while I lick my wounds from the pain of the time I lost being in my power. But I am waking up.We shrug and sigh when yet again another woman is raped, another girl is abused, another mother is beaten to a pulp, when in fact we should be fighting.Not fighting in the literal sense, but rather calling on the rage from the depths of our soul that was pushed down, “makeup upped”, swallowed, subdued, ignored, downplayed... that was asked to play nice and sit pretty like a good little girl.Fuck nice and fuck pretty.. it is boring, sad and leads to an unlived life.What is your greatest asset?#womenempowerment #femaleempowerment #revolution #feminism #anger #eatingdisorder #womenshealth

You thought that somebody else would save you,Hold you,Comfort you,And remind you of your worthiness..But nobody else can give you EXACTLY what you need right this very moment, other than YOU..I believe that people can inspire us and hold our hurting hearts when we need it the most..But the REAL CHANGE that your heart desires? It has to come from You..And I Understand your heart right now. You may be feeling hopeless,Helpless,Beaten down,And at the end of the road of Hope...But you have it in you right this very moment in time. I promise you this.Don't fall prey to the voice of your mind convincing you of all the reasons why you're just not good enough.Remember that last very special time when nobody thought you'd survive, AND YOU DID?.Dig deep for even an ounce of strength left within you. For as long as you're breathing, it's still there. You've always had it in you.You've simply forgotten.💫
Yeah I am smiling, but you are not the reason anymore.
I will fly. Chase the wind and touch the sky

Now, more than ever, friends have so much importance in our lives, for that unique support only a friend can give.At the same time, friendships can also become complicated. We can go through lots of ups and downs with each other in a friendship and it can be stressful or very upsetting when we drift due to whatever circumstances.I guess it reminds us that some friends will always be in our lives, but there will also be friends who are just with us for a short part of our life journey. Things I say to people dealing with grief, depression, and pain. ❤It can be really hard to know what to say to someone when they are hurting. Especially when you are also hurting or are hurting for them. At times like these, we just want to make them feel better, but can be afraid of saying something insensitive. Many times this fear or stress leaves us paralyzed and we repeat many clichés they've heard over time... even if sometimes we ourselves do not align with those clichés. ❤I hope this list helps you navigate your way in helping others with their pain and sadness. ❤Is there anything else you would add?*****#sabsrizviart

Sometimes it can be hard to know how to support a friend who may be struggling. We have some ideas that might help you reach out this #InternationalFriendshipDay.🔹 Ask your friend how they are feeling. They might not want to talk about how they are feeling or what is happening in their life. That is okay - but you are letting them know you care.🔹 Not everyone will want to be supported in the same way. Ask your friend what would help them the most. That way you know you are doing what they feel is best for them.🔹 Take time to listen to your friend - or book in time with them doing something they enjoy. If your friend opens up about how they are feeling, don't judge. Listen and be there for them. 🔹 Don't only talk about your friend's #MentalHealth. It is one part of their life. Make sure you still talk about the usual things you chat about, such as hobbies or shared interests, when your friend wants to.🔹 Opening up can be a big step in a friendship. Always show your friend respect and that they can trust you.🔹 Make sure to consider how you are feeling. Seeing and hearing someone you care about feeling unwell can be difficult. Tutti i Borderline sono diversi, ma una cosa accomuna tutti: la paura costante.Paura del futuro, di invecchiare, di essere "scoperti", di essere soli, di essere abbandonati. L'ultima ci porta a scappare prima che gli altri scappino.Eppure si tratta sempre e solo di sicurezze. Si tratta di parlare e non urlare, di voler trovare un punto in comune per quanto difficile sul momento possa essere.Si tratta di fare pace, di non dire quelle cose che feriscono, solo in un momento di rabbia. Di chiedere, e ricevere risposte chiare basate su rapporti solidi, almeno per l'altro.A volte basta poco per scacciare un brutto pensiero. Davvero poco.Eppure continuiamo ad elemosinare briciole, e il fatto di chiedere rappresenta in sé una risposta. Perché la fanno facile quando ti dicono che dovresti pensare al tutto, non alle parole, non alle frasi. Ma sono proprio quelle a mandarci a terra, così come ribadire ogni volta che hai sbagliato. As young kids, hope was all we had. We had hope for our future lives, hope that everything will be perfectly fine. That hope was not lost, it was simply misplaced. When life showed us what we didn’t expect as kids we turned our attention away from the hope we had so deeply. Sometimes people, events, trauma, and pain make our hope for ourselves and life lessen. We misplace our hope. Our negative experiences make us feel as if there’s no other alternative to a life of pain. But what we don’t realize when we’re feeling pain is that there’s another side of it. The healing and releasing of the pain. The gratitude for the pain after it. Where hope is re-instilled into ourselves. Realizing that we are resilient and the pain that once held us back is now one that pushes us forward. Hope has returned back to its rightful place after gaining confidence in pushing through adversity. Hope is not lost, simply misplaced. #mentalhealth #mentalhealthawareness #mindset #mindsetshift #mindsetcoach #mindsetiseverything #mindsetmatters #selfcare #selflove #selfesteem #selfconfidence #selfdevelopment #selfhelp #selfimprovement #selfacceptance #selfgrowth #selfworth #selfreminder #selfawareness #selfrespect #loveyourself#pain #sorrow #cry #depression #hope #hopeful #hopenotlost #therapeuticmentality

Growing up means learning what life is. When you're little, you have a set of ideals, standards, criteria, plans, outlooks, and you think that you have to sit around and wait for them to happen to you and then life will work. But life isn't like that, for anybody; you can't fall in love with a standard, you have to fall in love with a person. You can't live in a criteria, you have to live your life. You can't wait for your plans to materialize, because they may never materialize the way you think they will. You can't wait to watch your ideals and standards walk up to you, because you can't know what's yours until you have it. I always say, always take the first chance in case you never get a second one, but growing up takes that even one step further, growing up means that you have to hold on to what you have, when you have it, because what you have- that's yours- and all the ideals and criteria you have set in your head, those aren't yours, because those haven't happened to you.-C. Da qualche tempo frequento un ragazzo. Sono felice, forse troppo. E questo mi sconvolge, sono così felice da essere triste.Ho abbandonato una precedente relazione con un narcisista, fatta di false promesse e speranze da parte di entrambi. I cambiamenti mi turbano, lasciare la confort zone, se mai ne avessi avuta una. La sensazione di non essere più a casa, ma nella solita cristalliera dove poter far cadere tutto al primo movimento. A volte paragono le due storie, mi chiedo se anche questa finirà con me che scappo via senza dire niente, senza un saluto o una spiegazione. Se finirò a pensare che era la cosa migliore, che infondo se lo meritava.Oggi mi sveglio, e tra poco andrò a lavoro. È inutile dire che dopo una notte in cui non ho dormito ho una faccia orribile. È inutile dire anche che lavoro a contatto con il pubblico, che dovrò sorridere ed essere simpatica. Almeno, questo è quello che vorrei.In realtà mi alzerò per sistemarmi, farò ancora un pianto per cercare di espellere tutto il male col contagocce e ascolterò canzoni tristi in macchina. Mi attende una giornata di mutismo generale, spero solo di non diventare anche rabbiosa ed impaziente. Vorrei davvero non dover vivere questa giornata. Dal delirio della notte insonne mi è rimasto un gran malditesta, forse è per questo che già so che durante la risalita ogni piccolezza mi darà fastidio, e probabilmente sarà così per qualche giorno.Spesso penso di avere qualcosa nel cervello. Day 4 - Eureka to FlorenceAfter exploring Arcata, a charming town just north of Eureka where we saw a gorgeous Victorian home used in the film #TheLoveWitch and a burger shack that inspired the Krusty Krab in #SpongeBob, we took a break at Moonstone Beach 🌙 where my pea soup green puffer coat matched the local seaweed. Afterwards, we spent time in Redwood National Park 🌲where we saw elk and banana slugs!This was the first day where we encountered an issue, as the road between the park and the next city was intermittently closed because of a rockslide 😱 we were not deterred, though, and blew into the Oregon Coast like the marine layer 🌫This stretch of Oregon had some major highlights for the day, including the Natural Bridges near Pistol River, the Sisters Rocks 🪨, and the insane Oregon Dunes. The great drifts of sand felt utterly otherworldly, rising out of the lush greenery unexpectedly and serving as a stark contrast to the rugged cliffs and sea stacks that dominate most of the Oregon Coast. It is no wonder they inspired the sci-fi classic novel #Dune by Frank Herbert ✨ James and I were certainly in awe!

THE MOMENT WE ASK FOR HELP, WE RELINQUISH THE PERCEIVED CONTROL OF HANDLING EVERYTHING OURSELVES. ⁣⁣and it can be effing terrifying. ⁣⁣i remember this very clearly on the day before i quit drinking. i had been carrying on for years as if i was completely in control. ⁣⁣“i’ve got this. it’s all good. don’t worry about me. i’m solid.”⁣⁣until one day it was just undeniable that i wasn’t. ⁣⁣the moment it occurred to me to ask for help, a pit in my stomach sunk deep. as soon as i uttered the words, i would need to trust and potentially even listen to someone else’s guidance. ⁣⁣the terrifying terror of sharing my fate with someone other than myself! someone (or many someones) who couldn’t possibly do as good a job with my life as me. ⁣⁣asking for help shatters our delusion that we are okay as we are, alone in our own private jail. we convince ourselves it’s not so bad in there. at least we alone make the rules… ⁣but love, it’s lonely. isn’t it?⁣⁣it’s exhausting and depleting and soul-crushing to do it all alone. i know it’s scary to trust another person, but the relief is worth it. at least for me it is. ⁣⁣the day i asked for help my life changed. the past 6 1/2 years have been the best of my life. ⁣⁣what might you need help with that is holding you hostage?⁣⁣i know it’s scary. just pick the most un-scary person you know (even if it’s still scary to think about sharing your burden with them) and ask for help. ⁣⁣the words may burn as they leave your mouth, but it gets easier. ⁣⁣and then it gets amazing. and then doors open you had no idea were even there. ⁣⁣it’s worth it. ⁣it’s worth it. ⁣it’s worth it. ⁣⁣i love you. you are bigger than your fear. you are in charge of your own becoming. ⁣⁣much love, n. 🔥#control #outofcontrol #help #helpme #askforhelp #relationships #trust #trustissues #selflove #selfcare #selfhelp #selfworth #lonely #grow #growthmindset #growth #quotes #quotestoliveby #quotesaboutlife #quoteoftheday #quotestagram #inspirationalquotes #instadaily #empoweringwomen #empowerment #empoweredwomenempowerwomen #empoweringquotes #mindset #mindsetiseverything #mindsetmatters

The video What if when you die, you get shown a video of the life you could have lead if you believed in yourself, if you tried harder for what was important to you and if you prioritised your happiness. Would you be sad and jealous at what you missed out on or would you be content with all you achieved? Although this is a macabre thought, it is an excellent way to refocus and realise that the time to change is now. Are you living the life you have the potential to live? Is this your best life? And if not, are you actively striving towards that? Remember, as long as you are alive you are a decision away from positive change. What would you like to see on that video where you are the protagonist and the director? I wont say “live every day like it’s your last” because that is disgustingly cliché. We all have to deal with jobs, financial constraints, errands and difficulties. But I will say that we should aim for there to be moments of joy on most days, have a low tolerance for bs,  go after what we want, face our demons and get rid of what suppresses our soul. ❤️ & ✨#astrangeronatrain  #advice #love #relationships #psychology #risks #truth #selflove #mentalsupport #support #breakup  #mentalhealth #problemsolving #help #romance #friends #friendship #copingmechanisms #selfawareness #selfimprovement #improvement #opinion #strength #philosophy #quotes #noregrets

“WE ARE INCREDIBLY FORTUNATE PEOPLE”John Guzzardo 1972 - 2021These are the words my husband John would say to me at least once every week.And it was true. We have a nice house in a nice neighborhood, we were all happy and healthy, and we never took anything for granted. John loved his work and excelled in it. Dew-Drenched Furze (1889) by John Everett Millais.This late landscape is a visionary evocation of nature. Within a symmetrical composition and vertical format, light filters through the trees. According to his son J.G. Millais, Millais’s inspiration was “the potent voice of the wood spirits”. Millais’s title comes from Tennyson’s In Memoriam A.H.H., 1850, written in response to the early death of the poet’s friend Arthur Hallam. Millais may also have shared Tennyson’s opinion that, though a work may be inspired by personal experience, its emotions are universal: «“I” is not always the author speaking of himself, but the voice of the human race speaking through him.»From Alfred Tennyson, In Memoriam A.H.H., XI, 1850:Calm is the morn without a sound,Calm as to suit a calmer grief,And only thro’ the faded leafThe chestnut pattering to the ground:Calm and deep peace on this high wold,And on these dews that drench the furze,And all the silvery gossamersThat twinkle into green and gold:Calm and still light on yon great plainThat sweeps with all its autumn bowers,And crowded farms and lessening towers,To mingle with the bounding main:Calm and deep peace in this wide air,These leaves that redden to the fall;And in my heart, if calm at all,If any calm, a calm despair:Calm on the seas, and silver sleep,And waves that sway themselves in rest,And dead calm in that noble breastWhich heaves but with the heaving deep..#tatemuseum #dewdrenched #furze #natureart #nature #forest #trees #poetry #darkforest #solitude #enchantedforest #melancholy #oiloncanvas #painting #artdaily #artwork #artoftheday #darkart #atmospheric #landscape #oilpainting #darkcottagecore #darkaesthetic #johneverettmillais #whimsical #whimsicalart #fairycore #forestcore  #aquitestyle #landscapeart

Night (c.1854) by Louis-Rémy Robert.Louis Robert (1810–1882) grew up at the royal porcelain factory at Sèvres; his father was the head of the glass-painting atelier, a position that Louis himself assumed at the age of twenty-two, following his father’s death. In 1847, he was named head of the painting workshop, and in 1871 Director of the Manufacture. Inclined by training and temperament toward endeavors that brought together the fields of painting and chemistry, Robert was among the earliest French artists to take up paper photography, around 1850. After Regnault, an important chemist and pioneering photographer, became director of the porcelain factory in 1852, Robert’s photographic activity intensified, no doubt because the two men experimented together and encouraged each other’s work.In addition to the talented designers, artisans, and chemists who produced elaborate creations at the factory, the village of Sèvres attracted the naturalist painters Troyon, Daubigny, and Corot, who came to sketch picturesque scenes along the banks of the Seine and in the nearby forest. Robert knew them and, no doubt, drew inspiration from their paintings and drawings. His oeuvre consists of portraits of his family and friends, still lifes of the products of the porcelain factory, a series of landscapes made in the nearby gardens of Versailles and Saint-Cloud, a commissioned series of architectural studies of Brittany, and a group of views made at Romesnil in Normandy..#night #louisremyrobert #artoftheday #nudeart #vintageaesthetic #vintage #retro #picturesque #romanticism #vintagepaper #1854 #vintageart #art #artwork #artinspiration #darkart #darkaesthetic #artdaily #normandy #frenchartist #mystery #mystical #romanticdarkness #melancholy #atmospheric #artgram #romantic #louisremyrobert #arts #vintagepaper #artinspiration #art #arte #classicart

Domgård - Rót (2019)Блэк-метал из Швеции, более чем андерграундный, это их крайний альбом 19 года. Абсолютная нордическая тьма. Domgård был основан в 1997, однако от прежнего состава почти ничего не осталось, в музыкальном смысле они сильно изменились, однако атмосфера и посыл тот же. Старые участники были известны поджогами церквей и отсидкой в тюрьме, а также историями с гопниками, которые к ним прикапывались из-за длинных волос, одного из них однажды Domgård избили, если не убили. Старый вокалист совершил самоубийство. Однако для меня впервую очередь Domgård это атмосфера, очень холодная и негативная, разрушительная, самое то слушать их музыку здесь в Заполярье, недалеко от Норвегии в холодное время. Это тот момент когда открываешь для себя коллектив, который содержит в себе все за что ты полюбил жанр - это атмосфера холода и севера очень напоминающая Darkthrone и Burzum, это негатив и ненависть схожая с Shining, тоже шведской разрушительной командой, это использование германо-скандинавских образов и символов, и что ещё интереснее, музыка посвящена  хаос-гностицизму, каософии, то есть антикосмическому сатанизму, Шведы в принципе любят эту тему, неудивительно, там это все и зародилось. Сейчас в группе участники шведских Grá, Dark Funeral и ещё других команд. Этот альбом я выделяю особенно ибо здесь они взяли всю тьму и музыку своего творчества и создали ещё более качественный и цепляющий материал. Трек Sejdmannens Drömmar вообще раздирает душу, очень меланхолично и больно. Portraits- by Lea Tsaava • I look at photography as a separate world, as plots, and my models are the characters of these stories. Often processing photographs to music, images emerge and develop, they come to life. I love when people cry in my pictures. I think it's beautiful. Often it looks like tears of happiness and it is beautiful. I really like to work with complex light, light is a tool and light is the basis of the plot of any shooting. With the help of light on my set, the character (model) captures the mood and immerses herself in her character.I don't know if this is correct, but I also immerse myself in photography. In the frame, I am an observer from above, I follow the plot that I myself created while being a little detached. It’s such a fragile world and when I’m in it, reality almost doesn’t exist for me.art dir./photographer @lilsteeerrrmua @13_helga_13style @cote_basquemodel @berlyichik...#warriorswithincollective #magazine #blog #art #artistsoninstagram #artist #artwork #womensupportingwomen #published #friyay #cry #reality #photography #photo #photoofday #photographer

I had such a cry last night! It’s been an emotional month, but it only hit me last night what has happened in my life!  3 years ago, I was trying to work out HOW on Earth I could make it all work, ever! 😫If at any point kids aren’t well then what? When they start school and have half terms and school holidays to cover then what?! 😰Oh yes, I hear you, I could be a stay at home mum and settle for less, but taking such financial cut would be quite restricting for us, and also simply put not what I wanted for myself and for family! 💛Last night, I realised, that SOMEHOW… with all of this craziness happening in the world overshadowing everything else… I am now living through our first school summer holidays!!! Two weeks into it now and I have ONLY JUST NOTICED!?!? 🙈😮And yes, we’re having a blast! We can go on trips out, spend our days having fun in the garden, or be meeting friends, exploring, or just do whatever it is that we fancy on the day! I have so much to be grateful for my heart could burst! 💗It is exactly what I dreamed would be amazing to be able to do!! 💞I live the life I wished for! I love every day spend with Oscar now he’s not at school and time is so so precious! 💝 This first ever school summer holiday will never happen again! 🙊How did I not notice!? 🙄And I’ve been told that I was lucky to be able to enjoy being with my kids so much! That’s sweet… but no, I’m NOT LUCKY! I made this decision and I made this happen! ✌️ Super grateful to have been introduced to the opportunity where I could create this, but it was me staying up that bit later, getting up that bit earlier, going through obstacles, growing as a person, getting out of my comfort zone and not giving up ✌️Let’s not confuse ‘lucky’ with ‘committed’…My heart if full of gratitude to so many amazing people! And I am really proud of us all, of myself and super excited for all the good that’s coming 🙌Here’s to a Happy Summer Holidays, filled with incredible memories 🥂🍾xx#schoolholidays #summerholidays #grateful #proud #notlucky #makeyourluck

Depression is a cruel and quite frankly evil illness. It makes you long to connect with friends, makes you feel like everything would just be okay if you just sent that text to them, that one you've been trying to compose for hours,days. That their life is better without you, that they don't need you. It's your own fault you feel this way, your weak, your pathetic, your not worth their time, their love. Life update: We are moving. I was afraid we wouldn’t find a place and that my subsistence income would stop and I would be homeless but it all turned out. But I only felt relief for maybe a second. I’m  like that woody Allen character in one of his movies that finds out he doesn’t have cancer, is relieved for a second, then remembers that he hates life. I’m trying to be hopeful and now that I am able to survive maybe that’s possible but it often feels overwhelming and pointless. Surviving isn’t living. Even if I find a place fir myself, go places that make me hallucinate and have anxiety, make friends, our species is on a path to self destruction. #hopeless #hopeful #sad #emomgee #ozmosisjthomas #idontwanttodoanything

(Joshua 13: 1)When God makes you a promise, it will always be better than you had planned. Even though those wilderness periods tries there best to drain our strength, we must never lose hope in His promise.For over 40 years Isreal wandered around the wilderness as a nation without a home. The wilderness was their place of testing and as you already know it didn't go so well; an entire generation died off because of lack of trust and disobedience. But God had already made a promise, and now it was the next generations' season to reap. Under the leadership of Joshua, the children of Israel went from homelessness to conquerors. They had already conquered 31 kings and took the lands for themselves - they had more land than their hearts could have wished for, but God wasn't done. With 31 kingdoms now their homes, God said there still remains very much land still to be possessed. God was making His presence known through the blessings of His people. It doesn't matter about your past or your present; your education or lack of one; age, race or gender, when God says it's your time to reap a promise, all will clear out your way - for He is the One who open doors that NO man can close.Don't ever let go of the promise God gave you! Keep it in your heart and pursue it! ‘Hopeless’ - Colleen Hoover🌸🌸🌸 I should’ve learnt a long time ago that no author gets me back into reading like Hoover does. Every book I read of hers goes straight into my favourites. I’m happy to say this one was no different. It follows Sky falling for Dean Holder, but with their love comes the consequence of secrets that used to be well hidden. It was a tense read, full of love whilst also taking you on a road of suspense and doom. The ending was beautiful, leaving a conclusion that was very much a need and a want. Holder was the dream book boyfriend even when he was hiding secrets that would change Sky’s life forever. He was also there to pick up the pieces when the truth came out. It was one of them books that reveal why it’s called what it is so soon on, but doesn’t give the back story until much later and I absolutely loved it. One of my favourite reads this year by far. Cannot recommend it enough. Please read TW; sexual assault is prominent theme near the ending of this book. ‘Her tears are now falling even harder than my own. We wrap our arms around each other and we cry. We cry mother to daughter. We cry aunt to niece. We cry victim to victim. We cry survivor to survivor.’ 71/150🌸🌸🌸 #hopeless #losinghope #verity #uglylove #cohort #coho #cohobooks #colleenhoover #colleenhooverbooks #authorssupportingauthors #bookhaul #bookstagram #bookblogger #mustread #obsessed #book #reader #readerofinstagram #reading #yareview #yabookshelf #yabookreviews #yabooks #readmorebooks #readingtime #readerproblems #booklover #book⭐army #bookstagrammer #bookstagrammeruk

BOOK REVIEW 📖Hopeless By Colleen Hoover Rating: 5⭐️-Amazing!“The things that knock you down in life are tests, forcing you to make a choice between giving in and remaining on the ground or wiping the dirt off and standing up even taller than you did before you were knocked down.”I’m not crying you are! Oh my goodness this book had me in tears for the whole last part! It’s such an emotionally sad story about a girl who finally remembers the past she blocked out for thirteen years. This book has not been given enough credit in the book community in the love of Colleen Hoover books. It definitely beats a few of the books I’ve read by her now. I highly suggest this one if you haven’t read and it absolutely love Colleen Hoover. But be prepared to cry. This book is available to kindle unlimited subscribers. TW: Rape. Kidnapping. Description:Sometimes discovering the truth can leave you more hopeless than believing the lies…That’s what seventeen-year-old Sky realizes after she meets Dean Holder. A guy with a reputation that rivals her own and an uncanny ability to invoke feelings in her she’s never had before. He terrifies her and captivates her all in the span of one encounter, and something about the way he makes her feel sparks buried memories from a past she wishes could just stay buried. Sky struggles to keep him at a distance knowing he’s nothing but trouble, but Holder insists on learning everything about her. After finally caving to his unwavering pursuit, Sky soon finds that Holder isn’t at all who he’s been claiming to be. When the secrets he’s been keeping are finally revealed, every single facet of Sky’s life will change forever.#Bookstagram #BookReview #ColleenHoover #Hopeless #LosingHope #BooksOf2021 #BookRecommendations #CoHo #CoHoChallenge #ContemporaryRomance #Romance #KindleBooks #KindleUnlimitedBooks

(Luke 22: 31-32)No matter how long we've been walking with God, we should always be mindful that spiritual warfare is never to be underestimated. In verse 31 Jesus calls Peter "Simon", even though it was Him who changed Peter's name in the 1st place, (John 1:42). But Peter was His spiritual name, Simon was his natural name and at the time Jesus was speaking to the natural side of Peter and the message He had for Peter was so serious that He called him by his natural name twice.Jesus wanted Peter to know that Satan desired to put him through a test, a serious test, one that Peter would later fail, but the Lord wasn't concerned with Peter passing the test (if He was He would have prayed for him to have victory), He was more concerned with what mattered the most, his faith. People often ask why didn't God just stop Peter from being tested in the 1st place? But how often does God stop any of us from bring tested? If God never allowed us to be tested, we would all be a weak bunch of Christians, unable to withstand the intensity of spiritual warfare. We may see Peter as a failure because he failed his test. But to God, Peter was a winner because his faith stayed in tact. It's our faith in God that makes us a winner and when we make the choice to keep our faith in spite of spiritual warfare, we grow stronger and prove to God that we are fit for service and able to handle His blessings!Don't quit because you failed or because you don't understand - that's exactly what the enemy wants you to do. He's the one who's telling you to quit. Even though you failed, even though you don't understand, you keep your faith! Don't ever lose your faith! I apologize ahead of time for the incoming rant but I gotta get it out. I'm so sick and tired of being told how great, and wonderful, and caring, and amazing I am and it all meaning absolutely nothing in the end. I'm tired of giving my all, putting forth every effort, going above and beyond to give and treat people with all the love, affection, honesty, respect, and time they ask for and want, but when it comes to how I feel, what I ask for, what I want,, it doesn't fucking matter. I get sidelined, pushed away, ostracized, and ignored. Then I'm the bad guy, the crazy one for being upset about it. For feeling hurt, and used, and just plain walked on. I am worth more than that. I am deserving of better than that. I deserve the same effort and energy I put in as does every other person. It's not selfish to ask for that. It's not wrong of me to expect to be treated as I treat others. Honestly, I'm just done with love. There are days when I am physically and emotionally exhausted. Who can relate? ⁠. ⁠For many reasons, navigating the roller coaster of life (largely including being a mom), I can be left DRAINED at the end of the day. ⁠. ⁠Last night was one such day. It was compounded by my husband coming home from work in the same space- exhausted. ⁠. ⁠I've talked about increasing your awareness around what you need, and honestly, last night, I don't think either one of us knew what we needed or how to support each other.⁠.⁠I could feel the energy between us being on the verge of an argument, purely because we didn't have any capacity left. ⁠. ⁠It wasn't until we were brushing our teeth together, did I realize what we needed. We had a small but paramount moment of LAUGHTER. That single moment made the entire day manageable by being able to release the tension built up in my body and laugh with my loved one. ⁠. ⁠I hope this helps you. Next time you feel overwhelmed and don't know what you need, try and PLAY with your partner and LAUGH. See how you feel after. It might just be that simple.

#realtalk : #summer seems to be the unhealthiest time of the year for me. #ironic right? This is when we #travel more, #eat out, #go #out so I #sleep less, #exercise less and I my health apps prove this. I also notice this affects my #energy and I don’t feel my #health is where I would like it to be, making me feel a little #upset. Does this happen to you too? If you do some research, you will find out this happens to many of us. .So based on a little research I did; here are some tips to stay #healthy this summer:* Print a calendar of each month and schedule healthy days or weekends where you make time to sleep and exercise. * Do not overbook yourself! Have off weekends where you take care and pamper yourself. #spa night anyone?* Revise it every week and list what you ‘need to’ accomplish on that #weekend and what is something you ‘want to’ do and make a schedule for the weekend. * Live in the moment. Take time to be present in whatever you do, this will help it register and make you #happy .Happy healthy summer everyone!#doctor #healthylifestyle #summervibes

The Dalmore es un whisky diferente, pues es el único calificado como «Luxury Single Malt Whisky» desde 1839, con colecciones que ascienden a los 1,3 millones de euros y botellas que han cruzado la marga de los 1,5 millones de euros..Pero, ¿cuál es la razón por la que este whisky es tan especial? Fácil, la firma es pionera en el añejamiento dentro de múltiples barricas, todas ricas en aromas y sabores diferentes. En algún momento, dentro de algunas de las barricas que utilizan para crear este apreciado whisky, se contuvieron litros de licores como Tío Pepe Jerez, lo que le otorga al producto final una serie de notas aromáticas y sabores que difícilmente pueden ser igualados. To adults, this task may look simple. We do it without thinking. Filling up the glass and knowing when to stop when it’s full.This is a skill that a child needs to learn and have opportunities to learn. Most parents shy away from letting their young child work with water… because let’s face it, it gets messy! Not only does this work develop hand-eye coordination, fine motor skills, self-discipline, handling a fragile item, problem solving skills but it is also introducing early mathematical concepts. Introducing concepts such as FULL, EMPTY, HALF, LESS, MORE. This child is learning all of this, while learning measurement, comparing volumes and observing motion. So much learning 🌻😍TIP for when you do water activities with your child at home: Only give your child enough water that you are comfortable with cleaning up.For example, if your child is learning to drink from a glass - don’t fill the glass up all the way to the top of even half. Just provide a small amount at the start.

On Wednesday I facilitated my first (sold out) group experience using by methods of therapeutic expressive arts 🎨📝. We explored the theme of play and used expressive art forms (movement, writing, drawing, speaking) as a means to connect deeper with oneself and with others. I am feeling extremely inspired + grateful for experience and for those who were brave enough to participate 💗.I’ve been thinking a lot about what brings me joy and it’s definitely rooted in gathering. I love bringing people together. I love helping people feel good. And I equally love helping people connect with themselves and others in a meaningful way. One aspect of gathering that is often overlooked is that it favours individuals who are on the extroverted side of the energy spectrum. This has always been a challenge for me - I grew up as a very shy kid. I was conditioned to be the ‘good girl’ and so expressing myself as an adult has been extremely difficult. There has been so much to unlearn.When I worked in corporate it was challenging to be myself and be a “team player” - what was expected was attending large networking events, mingling with executives and going out for team drinks. This was all extremely draining as an introverted empath 🥲.Can anyone else relate?!But this is corporate culture. Individuals are rewarded for speaking up and taking up space. For embracing small talk. This is all ok but but not everyone enjoys this - in fact what is often thought of as a reward can feel like punishment (speaking from personal experience)What can we do? 🤔For one we need to look at how we can create more energy-inclusive spaces - spaces that help people who are on the introverted end of the energy spectrum feel safer to be themselves and present.Part of what I’m here to do is restore balance in gathering ⚖️.My hope is to continue these group experiences on a monthly basis - either IRL or virtually. I will keep you posted on future dates 📆If you think this might be something that will benefit your team/workplace/friend group please DM me 🌻. I would love to help you restore balance and infuse creativity + connection in your spaces of gathering 🧡

Can I let you in on a something?I had a moment a couple of months ago. I was scrolling through my social media feed and a persistent theme kept bubbling up. Stress and unease. Struggle and frustration. Fatigue. It was all over my feed. I could feel the emotions of those in my community.Then the guilt set in. Curious 🤔 Why guilt? In a moment when others are struggling why was my response guilt. After a lot of consideration and conversation, I came to this realization. I was feeling guilty because I had a secret. A secret that I was being called to share. So here it is… during this last year, I have found JOY. Did you just roll your eyes 👀 ? I wouldn’t blame you if you did. It sounds cracked, I know. But stick with me here. In the midst of lockdowns, restrictions, ever changing rules and updates, online school and cancellations, I found JOY. I found it in the moments before the sun rises. When I get to work out from the comfort of my own home. In the FaceTime conversations with my mom and the phone calls with my BFF. In conversations with women who feel like soul sisters. In the porch drops offs. A midst the sweat of a #peloton ride. Even in sharing office space with my ♥️ and the 🐶.How? Stay tuned. I have something special coming up next week! I’m going to share with you how you can welcome in more JOY too!Intrigued? Want to be the first to know what I have planned? Drop me a note in the DMs. I’ll let you in on the what’s coming…

Last evening we went, me and the lake fairy, to have a picnic supper by a lake. There were creatures. I enjoy taking pics of creatures on things. Here are some: a Carder Bee, Bombus Pascuorum on a thistle. Marmelade hover fly on air. Some kind of Calligrapher hover fly on chicory. A Napoleon spider on an ox eye daisy. A Burnet Companion moth also on Weedknap. A very hairy caterpillar, possibly a fox moth, on a small oak sapling. A False oil beetle on ox eye. Furrow beetle wrapping up a fly on its web A beautiful damsel fly not in any kind of distress and finally beat us vitale eligans balancing delicately on a dandelion. #creatures #lake #fairy #picnic #insects #beetles #spiders #hoverfly #wildflowers #joyful #nature #naturephotography

**Mind, body & soul**How many times have you told yourself the same thing?* It’s wet out, I’ll do it tomorrow.* I’m too tired, I’ll do it tomorrow.* It’s too late now/ I don’t have time today, I’ll do it tomorrow.Sometimes it’s not about the weather, being tired or just being tired. Sometimes, it’s just lack of motivation. It’s easy to start something, it’s the ‘sticking to it’ that is the hardest part AND this applies to anything in life.If you’re uninspired or unmotivated there could be a number of reasons:* Do you have too much on your plate?* Do you have unrealistic goals?* Were you pushing yourself too hard/too fast?Go back to the start and find your ‘Why’. Ask yourself what your original reason to ‘start’ was and find a reason to push yourself.1. Make a goal and clearly decide what you want.2. Focus on the first step and don’t get overwhelmed.3. Reach out and ask for help if you need it.4. Keep plugging away every single day.Life is too short for regrets.Much ♥Susan#collectiveconsciousness #intensions #setintentions #thankful #greatful #blessed #appreciate #appreciation #mindbodysoul #reiki #reikimaster #reikimaster🙏 #lightworker #lightworker💫  #divinefeminine  #df #goodvibes #vibe #vibration #zumbafitnessinstructor #zin #martialartsinstructor #groupfitnessinstructor #tarotreader #oraclecardreader

James had his first dental visit today at Butler Pediatric Dentistry in Fullerton!  James usually does very well at the doctor’s office because he is always so curious about all of their tools.  So, I wasn’t too worried about his experience, but curious about how he would handle having someone look at his teeth. Kathy was our dental assistant and she was IN-CRE-DI-BLE.  She was so warm and kind and very patient with James.  When she wanted James to get into the examination chair, he got scared.  So, I was able to lay on the chair while James laid on me.  James is very mechanical and hands on and Kathy recognized that quality and used that as a tool in her examination - letting him hold instruments, helping her with the toothpaste, explaining each tool (a thousand times to him), and, even though we all had masks on, you could tell she was smiling the whole time. Dr. Butler then came in to take a look at James’ teeth, to see if I had any questions or concerns, and explained anything she noticed with James’ teeth and how we could adjust our cleaning regiment to help him have healthier teeth.  She too was IN-CRE-DI-BLE.  I really loved their energy and positivity - they really know how to be around children this young.  Dr. Butler allowed James’ to touch everything and use some instruments because she understood that having an environment that encourages curiosity is the best thing for children.  @butlerpediatricdentistry, you ladies are doing an amazing job, and thank you!  Keep it up!  We need more doctor’s offices like this! As an adult, I never thought I would say this, but I love this dentist! Without yall and God I  wouldn't have got threw this message from god alone!! But I want the world to see my miracle baby.What Gods Angel's looks like.My baby had a seizure for 1hr straight they gave her every Medication for seizures for adults and children.. my baby stopped breathing ..The machine was breathing for her.She was flown to the main Childrens Hospital campus and woke up twice trying to take the tubes and cords off her.. But they had to put her back to sleep cause if the breathing tubes came out she would not Make it. The Drs excepted her to wake up on her own at some point days later.They couldn't wake her  up ... they said she had to do it on her own.. my baby woke up at 1am that night.. they put her back to sleep.. cause she tried taken  the breathing tubes out again. And this time she tried getting out the hospital bed.I was so distraught and didnt know what to think. I felt like I was cut with a razor and my heart was snatched out my chest. I though i had to bury my baby. I dont ever wish this feeling on no one.. my baby kissed me before she seized out .. I felt she told me good bye!!!Love on your kids and family cause you never know when there time will expire!!! #godchild #godschildren  ##beautiful #blessed #greatful #faith #family #prayingwarrior #prayingfamily #loveyourkids #unconditionallove #life

It’s an experience that takes a lot of trust on both ends, the hairstylist and the person trusting them with there hair.  Sometimes it creates a real and true beautiful lifelong bond, that lasts forever. Part of this is being with them for both the happy times and the bad.  It’s the hardest to lose them.  They know and you know, that time is slipping when they are sick.  I miss this beautiful woman and other special souls I’ve had the honor to help and support over the years. The second picture is the last time I ever saw her and we both new that was the case. Our hope for the future and a time when we would meet again was what bonded us. Phenomenal WomanBY MAYA ANGELOUPretty women wonder where my secret lies.I’m not cute or built to suit a fashion model’s size But when I start to tell them,They think I’m telling lies.I say,It’s in the reach of my arms,The span of my hips, The stride of my step, The curl of my lips. I’m a womanPhenomenally.Phenomenal woman, That’s me.I walk into a roomJust as cool as you please, And to a man,The fellows stand orFall down on their knees. Then they swarm around me,A hive of honey bees. I say,It’s the fire in my eyes, And the flash of my teeth, The swing in my waist, And the joy in my feet. I’m a womanPhenomenally.Phenomenal woman,That’s me.Men themselves have wondered What they see in me.They try so muchBut they can’t touchMy inner mystery.When I try to show them, They say they still can’t see. I say,It’s in the arch of my back, The sun of my smile,The ride of my breasts,The grace of my style.I’m a womanPhenomenally.Phenomenal woman,That’s me.Now you understandJust why my head’s not bowed. I don’t shout or jump aboutOr have to talk real loud. When you see me passing,It ought to make you proud.I say,It’s in the click of my heels, The bend of my hair, the palm of my hand, The need for my care. ’Cause I’m a womanPhenomenally.Phenomenal woman,That’s me.Resource: The Poetry Foundation ⁣.⁣.⁣.⁣.⁣.⁣#angeladavis #art #blackexcellence #blackhistory #blackhistory365 #blackhistorymonth #blackpride #greatful #inspiration #inspirationalquotes #instagood #life #love #lovequotes #mayaangelouquote #mayaangelouquotes #motivation #motivationalquotes #photography #poetry #positivevibes #positivity #quoteoftheday #quotes #quotestoliveby #selfcare #selfcarethreads #selflove #success #writer via @hashtagexpert

A real friend is someone who walks in when the rest of the world walks out. My husband has been there for me through thick and thin(quite literally). He always stands by me especially if it’s something I feel strongly about even if it’s got something to do with his own family. He understands where I come from without fully understanding what I’ve gone through. I never feel the need to explain myself, I know he will always have my back! To me there is no better match for me than him! Can’t wait for him to come back from deployment!My kid thinks I hang the moon. I’m not just saying that because he’s my kid because I’ve seen a lot of parent relationships and nothing compares to my kid and I. He really is one of my best friends. I’m the parent who is laid back, if you don’t intentionally hurt someone then I don’t think EVERYTHING is a punishable offense. I like that he can be honest with me, he knows when I get onto him about something I mean it because it’s gonna get himself or someone else hurt. I let him be him! I am raising him EXACTLY the way I said I would raise my kid!! **My mom hasn’t always been my “best friend” we’ve had our moments trust me! But now I don’t know what I’d do without her **Last but not least these ladies 😍😍 I don’t know how I’d make it at this base let alone work without them!!!#friendsforever #friends #friendship #love #friendshipgoals #bestfriends #life #husbandandwife #motherdaughter #friendsforlife #memories #bestfriend #boymom #deployedlife #fun #bff #usafwife #photography #forever #happy #best #friendshipquotes #smile #socialanxiety #funny #friendships #party #ever #cute #bhfyp

Last night was a bit chaotic. Around 2am I noticed our stringer lights outside had turned off on their own. As I looked out of our bedroom window, a constant flicker of heat lightening revealed the forest floor was moving. I thought I was hallucinating, or having another flood nightmare.. so I grabbed a flashlight and opened our front door. The water was already up to our second step and almost to the top of the camper tires.After some intense scrambling we waded through the thigh high water and to our vehicles, which were right in the middle of where the driveway was being washed out. We drove up to higher ground and waited. About half an hour later the water had already receded most of the way and I took this short video.A lot of folks in Carlisle lost their homes last night. We're extremely lucky our camper didn't get washed away or flooded. We have a lot of cleaning up to do, but damn are we lucky.#flashflood #rain #rainingcatsanddogs #flooded #creek #wtf #fortunate #extremelylucky #extremeweather #nightmare #kentucky #ky

I achieved one of my goals that I set for 2021 and I passed my DPS road test achieving my ultimate goal of getting my license again, which means I’m officially cleared to drive after my severe traumatic brain injury!!!!!!-I’ve been waiting almost 7 years for this, not realizing that getting behind the wheel again would be possible that whole time up until only a few months ago after going through extensive testing making sure neurologically, I was okay to drive again like testing my reaction time, decision making, and etc.-Once I passed all those tests, I only had to worry about the physical aspect of driving with just my left side so I was referred me to @strowmatt_rehab that got me trained on how to use the adaptive equipment and ultimately got me ready for my DPS road test.-I was nervous when the DPS official got in the car with me to start the test like I was about to play a big tennis match 😂 but I told myself “chill out, you know what you’re doing and this is what you have been working your butt off all these years for!!”-I don’t think it has quite hit me yet until I go CAR SHOPPING next week!!! I never thought I would say those words again 😬🙏🏽 Special thanks to Strowmatt Rehabilitation Services for getting me prepared with all those driving training hours getting used to the equipment and special thanks to my family for supporting me to achieve this goal!!-Now it’s time to go CAR SHOPPING!!! All the praise and glory goes to God 🙏🏽🙏🏽🙏🏽🙏🏽

BLAST FROM THE PAST. If you know me, I’m not a biggie on the past… except when it comes to reconnecting with gems like Carlos. We went to high school together in Miami and pretty much haven’t spoken in close to 30 years. I’ve been working on getting out of my head and beyond my social anxiety with @itsrogroh and her resources with @lets_cutclass. I saw her Masterclass and a term called a dormant tie— that’s somebody that you used to know and through the years you lost track of each other. I’ve been going through my FB friends and reconnecting with old friends. At first it was awkward AF!!A couple months ago I reconnected with Carlos. Which turned into a podcast, then a potential business collaboration (that just so happens to be in a social impact conversation we are both impassioned by), and today’s surf session. I also got to meet his son today… looks just like Carlos did back in the day. Huh. Dormant ties. So incredible, who knew?!#oldfriendsarethebestfriends #blastfromthepast #highschool #reunion #miami #network #community #letscutclass #dormantties #friends #friendsandbusiness #socialimpact

❤Personal Life Post❤I feel like going crazy.. my head hurts, my emotions are all over.. Im tired... this girl is very much walking on coffee fumes... We are busy with our residency at the moment, got a case officer end of June and we are nearing end of July...It is paperwork after paperwork, question after question, driving from one place to the other to get papers certified to send back to immigration...I was looking forward to receive a case officer because what a wait.. it has been 2 years.. with Covid and the backlog at immigration it made it even more stressful...This is not easy.. to pack up and leave everything you know, your family, your home, your life as you have build it.. yes we made that choice.. we want a better life for the kids.. a everyday life where the kids can be kids, and we have more freedom to not have to look over our shoulders everyday and live in fear..I pray that our application gets approved to get to stay in NZ and make it our permanent home.. this is no easy task.. you get taken apart, just for them to see your insides and if you are worthy to stay..Thankfully we have amazing family and friends, an amazing and wonderful God, without a support group to build you up, keep sending you good vibes, to put you back together.. we would not make it.. 🤞🏻Hoping for the best..and may this crazy emotional ride be a lesson and a prep run to make us more thankful for what we have in life..#personal #move #immigration #noteasy #goodvibes #emotional #crazy #blessed #feelingdrained #tired #keepingthefaith#family #friends #loved

¿Sabías que hoy es el Día internacional de la amistad?.👋🏻El 30 de julio se celebra en todo el mundo el Día Internacional de la Amistad, en honor a ese sentimiento desinteresado que es capaz de unir a personas muy diferentes, romper fronteras y tender lazos de solidaridad. Es tan poderoso por su naturaleza misma de bondad e incondicionalidad.👏🏻El reconocimiento oficial de esta efeméride ha sido iniciativa de la Asamblea General de Naciones Unidas en el año 2011, cuando proclamó el 30 de julio como el Día Internacional de la Amistad, a propuesta de la Cruzada Mundial de la Amistad.❤️El objetivo de la ONU es transmitir este sentimiento como una herramienta para conseguir la paz, acabar con la violencia y la pobreza, contribuyendo a una sociedad más justa y sostenible. En definitiva, que haya armonía dentro de los pueblos y entre ellos..👉🏻 Fuente Días Internacionales.#Guapasyapoyadas #diainternacionaldelaamistad #amistad #friends #friendship #BuenosAires #Argentina

¡Conoce la importancia de que tus peques tengan amigos! Algunos países celebran hoy el Día Internacional de la Amistad, fecha instaurada por la ONU en 2011, para poner en valor esta importante relación. El vínculo de amistad con otros niños es esencial para el desarrollo emocional y social de tu peque, y esta necesidad comienza en el instante en que busca ese primer amigo para jugar, pues con él vive diversión y felicidad a la hora de jugar. Entre sus beneficios se encuentra: 👦🏻👧🏻 Comprensión progresiva de la lealtad y reciprocidad, pues empiezan a confiar en otras personas. 👦🏻👧🏻 Respeto, tolerancia y empatía. 👦🏻👧🏻 Resolución de conflictos: En la vida es importante que aprendan a poder resolver conflictos con diálogo, buscando una solución en conjunto y siendo conscientes de la importancia de cooperación. 👦🏻👧🏻 Negociacion: Con fin de evitar malos entendidos y seguir disfrutando, es importante que los niños desde pequeños aprendan a negociar con sus amigos. ¡Menciona a la mamá o papá del mejor amigo de tu hijo! 🌺 Aloha Friday! It’s Friendship Day and as the old Girl Scout song 🎶 goes, “Make new friends, but keep the old; one is silver, the other is gold.  A circle is round, it has no end; that’s how long I will be your friend.” ⁠⁠In our crazy busy lives nowadays, it’s sad that we often find that we can get to the end of the day and barely, if ever, reach out to our friends in any meaningful way.  If I could do anything, it would be to encourage you to reach out to one or more of your closest friends and not only wish them a Happy Friendship Day, but really let them know how much they mean to you. 🥰⁠⁠Let them know how they’ve impacted your life. 😘 No day is promised. Take this day and let it be an opportunity to reach out to as many friends as you can to let them know how blessed you are to have them in your life.  And certainly, if you can, make plans with them to get together, if not on Friendship Day itself, as soon as possible afterward. 💌⁠⁠One of my favorite memory involving my friends are times of laughter over a meal or just hanging out, or going surfing. 😂 You may know that I’m a business owner who creates value for my clients and students by making art that you can collect or create yourself, so that your home can be a haven.⁠⁠But, I’m also someone who loves ❣️ their friends because, life is so much better together! Many of you reading this are my friend and I want to THANK YOU for your friendship! ⁠⁠So, I want to know:  How do you like to enjoy time with your friends and what are you going to do to celebrate with them today?  Share your ideas and fun plans down in the comments, below.  Your comment might just motivate or inspire someone else to celebrate Friendship Day in a better way, too!⁠⁠📸  With some high school friends that we've kept in touch for about 35 years! Wow! Time flies!🦋⁠⁠
Enjoy your weekend ladies 💃

🌺 Aloha Friday! It’s Friendship Day and as the old Girl Scout song 🎶 goes, “Make new friends, but keep the old; one is silver, the other is gold.  A circle is round, it has no end; that’s how long I will be your friend.” ⁠⁠In our crazy busy lives nowadays, it’s sad that we often find that we can get to the end of the day and barely, if ever, reach out to our friends in any meaningful way.  If I could do anything, it would be to encourage you to reach out to one or more of your closest friends and not only wish them a Happy Friendship Day, but really let them know how much they mean to you. 🥰⁠⁠Let them know how they’ve impacted your life. 😘 No day is promised. Take this day and let it be an opportunity to reach out to as many friends as you can to let them know how blessed you are to have them in your life.  And certainly, if you can, make plans with them to get together, if not on Friendship Day itself, as soon as possible afterward. 💌⁠⁠One of my favorite memory involving my friends are times of laughter over a meal or just hanging out, or going surfing. 😂 You may know that I’m a business owner who creates value for my clients and students by making art that you can collect or create yourself, so that your home can be a haven.⁠⁠But, I’m also someone who loves ❣️ their friends because, life is so much better together! Many of you reading this are my friend and I want to THANK YOU for your friendship! ⁠⁠So, I want to know:  How do you like to enjoy time with your friends and what are you going to do to celebrate with them today?  Share your ideas and fun plans down in the comments, below.  Your comment might just motivate or inspire someone else to celebrate Friendship Day in a better way, too!⁠⁠📸  With some high school friends that we've kept in touch for about 35 years! Wow! Time flies!🦋⁠⁠

Hace 12 años exactamente estamos juntas, hemos pasado por altas y muy bajas, nos hemos peleado, llorado, reído, rumbeado, hemos estado juntas en los mejores momentos de nuestras vidas y en los peores también; Gracias a ti se que la palabra “amiga” no se le da a todo el mundo, pero luego que aprendí el significado, descubrí que eso para ti no era nada. Sin ti, yo no. 19 Maj 2016. Inte långt efter min olycka skrev jag hur jag kände. Jag mådde verkligen ej bra. Jag ville bara överleva. Jag trodde att en dag skulle allt vara över. Att jag skulle vara läkt, hel och vara migsjälv igen. Nu fem år efter olyckan så sitter jag än i helvetet. Vi gör allt som familj för att de ej ska se ut så utåt men ush va min kropp lider på alla sätt o vis. Jag har även blivit sjuk o ingen vet riktigt varför. En kamp jag även fått dras med sedan 2019. MEN jag kanske ej kommer tillbaka, detta kanske är mitt liv tills den dag jag ej finns kvar o därför har jag bestämt mig för att välja livet. Jag har ju egentligen ett väldigt fint liv, partner o barn. Så de är de jag väljer oavsett hur de än är. På bilden har Anya nyss kommit till världen, vi får se vår andra bebis för första gången o jag minns hur jag började prata om Ella direkt o hur @nfsnickeri tar sin hand på min arm o klämmer åt hårt utav lycka o hur min mamma @annkarlberg22 pustar ut över att allt fick bra, vi var klara vi var fulländade vi var den familj vi skulle vara för alltid. Tre timmar efter denna bilden tagits ligger jag ovetandes döende på ett operationsbord, en kamp som tog 7timmar. Jag överlevde men samtidigt så förlorade jag mitt liv den dagen ändå. De med spinal stenose må alltid opereres.Dette er en myte⚠️👉🏻 Du kan først prøve behandlinger som fysioterapi, medisiner, styrkeøvelser, diskografi og steroid injeksjoner.👉🏻 Symptomer ved spinal stenoseSymptomene kan variere avhengig av hvor stenosen oppstår og hvilke nerver som er berørte. Spinal stenose utvikler seg langsomt over mange år, og i begynnelsen er symptomene vage, men de vil bli verre.Spinal stenose i nakken:✅ Nummenhet eller kribling i en hånd, arm, fot eller ben✅ Følelse av svakhet i de samme lemmene✅ Problem med balansen når du går✅ NakkesmerterSpinal stenose i korsryggen:✅ Nummenhet eller kribling i en fot eller ben✅ Muskelsvakhet/svekket kraft i bena✅ Smerter eller krampe i bena når du står eller går lenge. Symptomlindring oppleves når du setter deg ned, eller når du bøyer deg forover og løfter foten opp på noe på høyde med en stol.✅ Ryggsmerter med utstråling til sete og lår eller leggerLes mer på vår nettside. DU ER SÅ JÆVLIG DEPRIMERENDE! Har jeg oppmerksomheten din nå? Fint!Så mange ganger ser jeg infuensere/instagrammere skrive "omgi deg med positive mennesker som gir deg energi".Denne setningen skremmer meg. Betyr det at de gangene jeg har det tøft og føler meg nedfor så skal jeg skjule det i frykt for at andre ikke skal like meg? For det er igrunn det denne setningen sier...Jeg forstår konseptet, og at positivitet avler positivitet, men sannheten er at ingen liv er rosenrøde hele tiden. Mennesker har det tøft. Folk går igjennom harde tider i livet. Og hver dag er ikke lik. Det må være lov å si at ting er drit uten redsel for å bli mislikt eller miste venner.  Sannheten er at det ER lettere å like glade mennesker, såklart er det det. Men gjør deg selv og andre tjenesten å ikke fronte at det kun er lykkelige, glade og sprudlende mennesker som gir verdi til livet ditt. Alle mennesker, uansett utgangspunkt og forutsetninger i livet har en verdi, og kan tilføre noe positivt til ditt dersom du lar dem. ❤️ #alleharverdi#ærlighet #samfunn #rosenrødt #alle #verdi #fitnessjourney #mentalhelse #mentaltrening #styrke #positivitet #energi #sannhet #glad #lykke #mamma #familie #family #livet #life #dubetyrnoe #blidhverdag #heiaossjenter #ekte #rørt #tenk #tanker #medmenneske #allemed #kjærlighet

Swipe left⬅️⬅️⬅️. Dit is mijn favoriete shampoo en conditioner🥰. + andere voorbeelden.💟Na een Keratine behandeling is het haar steil, pluisvrij, glanzend en sterk. Om het resultaat te behouden is een shampoo zonder sulfaten en parabenen een must! Alhoewel na een behandeling je haar erg sterk aanvoelt, kan dit na enkele maanden verdwijnen. Hierdoor zal de keratine zelf waarschijnlijk niet het probleem zijn. Het probleem ligt in het gebruik van (producten) in combinatie met andere ingrediënten.💟Kies daarom voor een shampoo zonder sulfaten en parabenen.💟Wat zijn dan sulfaatvrije shampoo's? Sulfaatvrije shampoo’s bevatten geen SLS (Sodium Lauryl Sulfate) of ALS (Ammonium Lauryl Sulfate). Het zijn twee chemicaliën die vaak in zeep en shampoo worden gebruikt. SLS dringt diep in je haar en zorgt ervoor dat oliën en vuil uit je haar worden verwijderd. Dit lijkt natuurlijk heel goed, omdat je haar er schoon van wordt, maar SLS verwijdert ook de natuurlijke haaroliën. Dit resulteert in droog haar. ALS doet eigenlijk hetzelfde als SLS, maar is een mildere vorm. Tegenwoordig vind je veel sulfaatvrije shampoo’s online of in de drogisterijen.💟Ook wanneer je geen keratine behandeling hebt gedaan zijn sulfaatvrije shampoos een aanrader voor kroes en krullend haar.💟BELANGRIJK: luister altijd goed naar uw haar. Wordt uw haar bijvoorbeeld heel droog van een bepaalde shampoo dan zegt uw haar dat ze die shampoo niet fijn vind. Stap dan over naar een andere shampoo en conditioner.💟Verwen uw haar altijd met haar maskers, oliën een deep conditner of een deep treatment voor extra voeding het haar.💟Maak direct een afspraak via een privé berichtje💌.#KeratinebyBeaulien #BeautyByBeaulien #Biologisch #Keratinetreatment #Semipermanent #Steil #Rotterdam #Braziliaansekeratinebehandeling #Keratinebehandeling #etos #kruitvat #LAELEGANCE #trekpleister #detuinen #Healftyhair #Verzorgd #Glad #Zacht #Keratine #Gezond #Glanzend #MooiHaar #Sexy #hask #Beautyfull #Prachtig #pluisvrij #schoonheid
